    "In Gottlieb & Ernst-Slavit's (2013) dimensions of academic language, Vocabulary is in the lowest line at word and phrase level.",
    "It, however, is never of the lowest importance.",
    "This is because academic writing has a higher level of Vocabulary in comparison to other types of writing.",
    "In academia, it is essential to equip students' competence to understand and use academic words correctly.",
    "Osmond (2016) argues that knowledge of academic Vocabulary ensures that writers produce texts that are understandable, eligible, and centered around the topics they wish to deliver to educated readers of the field."
